verses.text_plain: I will praise thee with my whole heart: before the gods will I sing praise unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 1I will praise thee with my whole heart: before the gods will I sing praise unto thee.

verses.text_plain: I will worship toward thy holy temple, and praise thy name for thy lovingkindness and for thy truth: for thou hast magnified thy word above all thy name.
verses.verse_html: 2I will worship toward thy holy temple, and praise thy name for thy lovingkindness and for thy truth: for thou hast magnified thy word above all thy name.

verses.text_plain: In the day when I cried thou answeredst me, and strengthenedst me with strength in my soul.
verses.verse_html: 3In the day when I cried thou answeredst me, and strengthenedst me with strength in my soul.

verses.text_plain: All the kings of the earth shall praise thee, O Lord, when they hear the words of thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 4All the kings of the earth shall praise thee, O Lord, when they hear the words of thy mouth.

verses.text_plain: Yea, they shall sing in the ways of the Lord: for great is the glory of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 5Yea, they shall sing in the ways of the Lord: for great is the glory of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Though the Lord be high, yet hath he respect unto the lowly: but the proud he knoweth afar off.
verses.verse_html: 6Though the Lord be high, yet hath he respect unto the lowly: but the proud he knoweth afar off.

verses.text_plain: Though I walk in the midst of trouble, thou wilt revive me: thou shalt stretch forth thine hand against the wrath of mine enemies, and thy right hand shall save me.
verses.verse_html: 7Though I walk in the midst of trouble, thou wilt revive me: thou shalt stretch forth thine hand against the wrath of mine enemies, and thy right hand shall save me.

verses.text_plain: The Lord will perfect that which concerneth me: thy mercy, O Lord, endureth for ever: forsake not the works of thine own hands.
verses.verse_html: 8The Lord will perfect that which concerneth me: thy mercy, O Lord, endureth for ever: forsake not the works of thine own hands.
